article.description: — Josh Jefferson had a career-high 25 points as Green Bay edged past Oakland 84-81 in overtime on Friday.
article.headline: Jefferson carries Green Bay past Oakland 84-81 in OT
article.linkText: Jefferson carries Green Bay past Oakland 84-81 in OT
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- — Josh Jefferson had a career-high 25 points as Green Bay edged past Oakland 84-81 in overtime on Friday. Amari Davis had 18 points for Green Bay (2-9, 2-5 Horizon League). PJ Pipes added 15 points and six rebounds. Jefferson made 8 of 10 shots and Green Bay posted a season-high 21 assists. Jalen Moore scored a season-high 33 points for the Golden Grizzlies (3-11, 3-4). Daniel Oladapo scored a season-high 20 points and had 18 rebounds. Rashad Williams had 15 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
